ulouse and one of Douady’s former doctoral students. “It was very exciting.”\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>A key part of the Orsay notes was a humble statement that would soon become the most important question about the Mandelbrot set: the MLC conjecture.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>MLC posits that the Mandelbrot set isn’t just connected; it’s locally connected — no matter how much you zoom in on the Mandelbrot set, it will always look like one connected piece. For instance, a circle is locally connected. An extremely fine-toothed comb, on the other hand, is not. Though the entire shape is connected, if you skip over the shaft and instead zoom in on the tips of some of its teeth, you’ll just see a bunch of separate line segments.\u003c/p>\n","fadein":null,"__typename":"ACFContent"},"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22":{"hide_this_component":null,"acf_fc_layout":"image_component","layout":"inline","regular_caption_right":true,"settings":"","attribution":"\u003cp>Merrill Sherman/\u003cem>Quanta Magazine\u003c/em>\u003c/p>\n","caption":"","mobile_comp_caption":"","mobile_comp_attribution":"","sets":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22.sets.0","typename":"ImageSet"}],"__typename":"ACFImageComponent"},"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22.sets.0":{"settings":"","image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22.sets.0.image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22.sets.0.mobile_image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_side_margins":false,"mobile_width_constraint":null,"mobile_caption":"","mobile_attribution":"\u003cp>Merrill Sherman/\u003cem>Quanta Magazine\u003c/em>\u003c/p>\n","zoom_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22.sets.0.zoom_image","typename":"Image"},"zoom_caption":"","zoom_attribution":"","mobile_zoom_image":null,"mobile_zoom_caption":null,"mobile_zoom_attribution":null,"external_link":"","__typename":"ImageSet"},"$Post:134276.acf.modules.22.sets.0.image":{"alt":"